1
00:00:10,677 --> 00:00:11,803
Morning.

2
00:00:27,152 --> 00:00:29,446
They're pickled just right.

3
00:00:29,488 --> 00:00:31,323
[crunching]

4
00:00:35,118 --> 00:00:37,246
Damn, this is good.

5
00:00:37,329 --> 00:00:40,332
Sanosuke,
you really have a knack

6
00:00:40,415 --> 00:00:43,502
for knowing exactly
when pickles are at their best.

7
00:00:45,504 --> 00:00:47,339
[crunching]

8
00:00:54,221 --> 00:00:55,639
Does it make a difference?

9
00:01:00,352 --> 00:01:03,313
A guy like you
will never get it.

10
00:01:04,022 --> 00:01:06,149
[all laughing]

11
00:01:08,819 --> 00:01:11,738
[♪♪♪]

12
00:01:45,105 --> 00:01:47,232
Got it.

13
00:01:49,109 --> 00:01:51,194
[Saito]
"Got it."

14
00:01:59,453 --> 00:02:01,121
[unenthusiastically]
Yah.

15
00:02:06,627 --> 00:02:08,086
"Got it."

16
00:02:08,170 --> 00:02:10,297
[laughing]
Just kidding.
It's a joke.

17
00:02:10,380 --> 00:02:12,591
I said it's a joke.

18
00:02:12,674 --> 00:02:14,593
[continues laughing]

19
00:02:17,512 --> 00:02:20,891
He's going to kill me! Got it.

20
00:02:20,974 --> 00:02:26,480
SONG OF THE SAMURAI

21
00:02:28,231 --> 00:02:32,277
Kamo. What is it
you wanted to discuss?

22
00:02:32,361 --> 00:02:34,905
Our very own Niimi
is connected with Choshu.

23
00:02:38,533 --> 00:02:42,496
Saeki Matasaburo is a Choshu
assassin, hired by Niimi.

24
00:02:43,955 --> 00:02:45,332
[Hijikata]
Saeki's an assassin?

25
00:02:45,415 --> 00:02:47,459
[Serizawa]
Right, and by the way...

26
00:02:47,542 --> 00:02:49,252
Niimi killed

27
00:02:50,754 --> 00:02:52,464
Abiru Eisaburo, too.

28
00:02:54,591 --> 00:02:57,844
[Matsudaira]
What are you going to do
about Niimi?

29
00:02:57,928 --> 00:02:59,429
Mm... Not a damn thing.

30
00:02:59,471 --> 00:03:01,431
I knew all along
and didn't do anything.

31
00:03:04,601 --> 00:03:08,313
[Sagawa]
If that's true, then you're
subject to punishment as well.

32
00:03:08,397 --> 00:03:09,815
[Serizawa]
I don't care.

33
00:03:09,898 --> 00:03:12,818
[Sagawa]
I'll cut you down
right here and now.

34
00:03:14,277 --> 00:03:17,155
[sighing]
If you want to kill me,

35
00:03:17,239 --> 00:03:19,783
you'd better
come at me with all you've got.

36
00:03:21,493 --> 00:03:22,411
Hey...

37
00:03:22,494 --> 00:03:23,870
[Sagawa]
What do you think you're doing?

38
00:03:23,954 --> 00:03:25,330
[Serizawa chuckling]

39
00:03:26,957 --> 00:03:29,459
Sorry. This one's my fight.

40
00:03:29,543 --> 00:03:32,921
Oh? Gotten a little stronger,
have we?

41
00:03:36,133 --> 00:03:37,676
[both chuckling]

42
00:03:39,845 --> 00:03:41,138
[groans]

43
00:03:41,179 --> 00:03:42,347
Take that!

44
00:03:46,017 --> 00:03:48,520
Great!
[groans]

45
00:03:49,855 --> 00:03:54,359
Let me go! I said let me go!

46
00:04:08,582 --> 00:04:09,958
[shouts]

47
00:04:11,334 --> 00:04:13,128
You really are as strong
as they say.

48
00:04:13,211 --> 00:04:15,922
Ooh... I like this.

49
00:04:16,965 --> 00:04:19,426
I smell violence on you...

50
00:04:19,509 --> 00:04:23,388
Right now, you might actually
be worth cutting down.

51
00:04:28,101 --> 00:04:30,395
[Serizawa] Hey!
Boss!

52
00:04:30,479 --> 00:04:32,773
If we're going to settle this
here and now

53
00:04:32,856 --> 00:04:35,192
then it only makes sense for me
to be your opponent!

54
00:04:35,275 --> 00:04:37,277
[Hijikata]
Don't get in the way!

55
00:04:50,123 --> 00:04:52,667
[yells fiercely]

56
00:05:04,137 --> 00:05:06,056
[yawning]

57
00:05:10,227 --> 00:05:12,896
Right now, you don't
do anything for me.

58
00:05:12,938 --> 00:05:13,939
What?

59
00:05:14,022 --> 00:05:16,483
Hey, you heard me.

60
00:05:16,566 --> 00:05:19,361
"Come at me
with everything you've got."

61
00:05:21,112 --> 00:05:22,572
[Serizawa scoffs, chuckles]

62
00:05:24,074 --> 00:05:26,993
When you're ready to get
serious, come back then. Okay?

63
00:05:28,411 --> 00:05:32,749
Aizu, too.
I'll take you on anytime.

64
00:05:35,961 --> 00:05:37,254
Thank you.

65
00:05:37,295 --> 00:05:38,755
[chuckles]

66
00:05:39,965 --> 00:05:41,424
[Matsudaira]
Hey, Kamo.

67
00:05:42,717 --> 00:05:43,802
[sighs]

68
00:05:45,929 --> 00:05:50,600
You really are one stubborn
son of a bitch.

69
00:05:52,352 --> 00:05:54,187
Takes one to know one, Boss.

70
00:05:54,271 --> 00:05:55,480
[chuckles]

71
00:05:57,983 --> 00:05:59,651
[Serizawa sighs]

72
00:05:59,734 --> 00:06:00,944
I'm leaving now.

73
00:06:05,949 --> 00:06:07,951
[Yamanami]
That was quite a surprise.

74
00:06:09,911 --> 00:06:12,873
Why would Serizawa
choose to go down with Niimi,

75
00:06:12,956 --> 00:06:15,834
knowing everything?

76
00:06:19,212 --> 00:06:20,964
I just don't understand it
anymore.

77
00:06:23,842 --> 00:06:26,136
He's simply more honest
than anyone else.

78
00:06:28,430 --> 00:06:29,681
Honest?

79
00:06:31,516 --> 00:06:32,934
That man...

80
00:06:34,811 --> 00:06:38,315
all he's ever done is live
his life searching for something

81
00:06:38,398 --> 00:06:40,692
that would set his blood
on fire.

82
00:06:45,864 --> 00:06:51,161
In his own way,
that man is also...

83
00:06:54,039 --> 00:06:55,874
a pure samurai.

84
00:06:58,543 --> 00:07:01,713
[♪♪♪]

85
00:07:33,578 --> 00:07:36,247
[footsteps approaching]

86
00:07:41,461 --> 00:07:43,004
[Hijikata]
Why did you get in my way?

87
00:07:48,134 --> 00:07:50,011
When you drew your sword...

88
00:07:51,638 --> 00:07:53,932
it wasn't to take down Serizawa.

89
00:07:56,851 --> 00:07:58,937
It was to protect me, wasn't it?

90
00:08:03,233 --> 00:08:06,069
Did you think
I was going to lose?

91
00:08:06,111 --> 00:08:07,112
[Kondo]
Yes.

92
00:08:08,989 --> 00:08:10,991
You must have known that,
too, Toshi.

93
00:08:15,453 --> 00:08:17,288
Why did you try
to cut Serizawa down?

94
00:08:22,419 --> 00:08:24,921
For the good of the corps,
obviously.

95
00:08:24,963 --> 00:08:26,256
Don't play dumb.

96
00:08:28,091 --> 00:08:30,260
You just wanted to fight him

97
00:08:30,301 --> 00:08:32,595
for your own satisfaction,
didn't you?

98
00:08:40,729 --> 00:08:42,939
Once you lose your head,
it's over.

99
00:08:44,315 --> 00:08:45,859
I've seen a man

100
00:08:47,152 --> 00:08:48,778
go down that path before.

101
00:08:54,534 --> 00:08:55,994
I don't want you

102
00:08:57,412 --> 00:08:59,080
to end up like him.

103
00:09:04,753 --> 00:09:06,546
But I still want that fight.

104
00:09:16,931 --> 00:09:18,016
You'll die.

105
00:09:24,189 --> 00:09:25,982
The weak die.

106
00:09:27,859 --> 00:09:29,819
That's all there is to it,
right?

107
00:09:33,448 --> 00:09:35,200
[sighs]

108
00:09:43,750 --> 00:09:45,877
That's how you are, Toshi...

109
00:09:51,382 --> 00:09:53,134
Are you any different,
boss?

110
00:09:56,554 --> 00:09:58,723
There's a strong opponent
facing you.

111
00:10:01,601 --> 00:10:04,104
And you want
to risk your life to fight him.

112
00:10:07,565 --> 00:10:09,067
You don't feel that?

113
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:18,993
[sighs]

114
00:10:41,683 --> 00:10:43,643
[coins clinking]

115
00:10:46,062 --> 00:10:47,105
Money?

116
00:10:47,188 --> 00:10:51,109
Money!

117
00:10:53,069 --> 00:10:56,573
Lord Katamori is aware
that the imperial edict

118
00:10:56,614 --> 00:10:59,659
is a forgery
plotted by the Choshu.

119
00:10:59,742 --> 00:11:03,037
The information
came from Satsuma.

120
00:11:07,250 --> 00:11:08,918
[Serizawa]
Hey, Niimi.

121
00:11:10,128 --> 00:11:11,212
Serizawa!

122
00:11:12,005 --> 00:11:13,089
Oh.

123
00:11:17,343 --> 00:11:18,845
[sighs]

124
00:11:21,055 --> 00:11:22,307
[sighs]

125
00:11:24,767 --> 00:11:27,854
Looks like things are getting
ugly for the Choshu, huh?

126
00:11:28,980 --> 00:11:31,774
Hm? This is all for me, right?

127
00:11:33,651 --> 00:11:34,736
Yes.

128
00:11:34,819 --> 00:11:38,114
But now, what to do?
What?

129
00:11:38,198 --> 00:11:41,618
The truth is, I already
told Katamori everything

130
00:11:41,701 --> 00:11:46,039
that you were connected
with Choshu

131
00:11:47,457 --> 00:11:49,667
and that you schemed with Kusaka
to take out Abiru and Aijiro.

132
00:11:49,751 --> 00:11:51,127
[chuckles]

133
00:11:51,169 --> 00:11:54,464
By the way, Kondo and the others
were there, too.

134
00:11:54,505 --> 00:11:58,760
Bet they'd risk it all
to kill you, don't you think?

135
00:12:00,803 --> 00:12:02,138
Serizawa.

136
00:12:03,848 --> 00:12:06,017
Does this mean
you've cast me aside?

137
00:12:07,518 --> 00:12:09,979
When did I ever say that?

138
00:12:10,063 --> 00:12:11,189
Then why?!

139
00:12:11,272 --> 00:12:17,237
I just want to see you
go head-to-head with them.

140
00:12:17,320 --> 00:12:19,364
Huh?

141
00:12:19,447 --> 00:12:22,200
[Serizawa]
I'm expecting
some spectacular violence.

142
00:12:25,578 --> 00:12:28,539
[♪♪♪]

143
00:12:37,382 --> 00:12:39,509
[fuming]

144
00:12:39,550 --> 00:12:42,679
[Hirayama]
So you're really going
to let Niimi handle this alone?

145
00:12:42,762 --> 00:12:44,764
[Serizawa grunts]

146
00:12:44,847 --> 00:12:46,432
Knowing him

147
00:12:46,516 --> 00:12:47,934
after he defeats them,

148
00:12:48,017 --> 00:12:51,020
he'll probably come
for you next, don't you think?

149
00:12:51,104 --> 00:12:52,355
[laughing]

150
00:12:52,438 --> 00:12:55,525
I like that. That's awesome.

151
00:12:55,566 --> 00:12:59,404
You see, when it comes
to violence versus violence...

152
00:13:00,738 --> 00:13:02,448
the more you pit it
against itself,

153
00:13:02,532 --> 00:13:04,075
the more refined it becomes.

154
00:13:07,078 --> 00:13:09,872
And the most exquisite part...

155
00:13:12,417 --> 00:13:14,335
I'll devour it myself.

156
00:13:19,924 --> 00:13:22,427
[chuckling]
Gets my blood boiling.

157
00:13:24,595 --> 00:13:28,516
[♪♪♪]

158
00:13:28,599 --> 00:13:30,143
[grunting]

159
00:13:36,649 --> 00:13:38,026
[sighing]

160
00:14:20,985 --> 00:14:25,156
[♪♪♪]

161
00:14:28,868 --> 00:14:30,620
[narrator]
At the same time

162
00:14:30,661 --> 00:14:33,539
the Aizu clan joined forces
with the Satsuma clan

163
00:14:33,623 --> 00:14:37,085
and completely sealed off
the Imperial Palace.

164
00:14:37,126 --> 00:14:41,422
The Mibu Roshigumi was also
dispatched to guard the palace.

165
00:14:42,882 --> 00:14:45,802
As a result of this coup d'état
on August 18

166
00:14:45,885 --> 00:14:50,973
the seven Sonno Joi nobles
ruling the court

167
00:14:51,015 --> 00:14:55,019
and the Choshu forces,
were expelled from Kyo.

168
00:14:57,772 --> 00:14:59,232
[Kusaka]
Halt!

169
00:15:02,026 --> 00:15:07,031
This is not a rout!

170
00:15:08,950 --> 00:15:11,035
It is a strategic withdrawal.

171
00:15:11,911 --> 00:15:15,039
Justice is on our side!

172
00:15:19,335 --> 00:15:20,336
Mark my words

173
00:15:21,754 --> 00:15:26,300
the day will come when we return
to the capital in triumph!

174
00:15:28,511 --> 00:15:32,640
But there's one thing
we should've taken,

175
00:15:32,723 --> 00:15:35,518
no matter the cost.

176
00:15:35,560 --> 00:15:38,312
The head of Matsudaira Katamori.

177
00:15:38,396 --> 00:15:41,315
[♪♪♪]

178
00:15:44,402 --> 00:15:47,280
[narrator]
After this political upheaval

179
00:15:47,363 --> 00:15:49,949
the Mibu Roshigumi
were officially tasked

180
00:15:50,032 --> 00:15:52,702
by Lord Katamori
with patrolling the city

181
00:15:52,785 --> 00:15:54,829
and were bestowed a new name.

182
00:15:54,912 --> 00:15:57,665
[clamoring]

183
00:16:00,293 --> 00:16:01,502
That name

184
00:16:02,712 --> 00:16:04,797
was the Shinsengumi.

185
00:16:04,881 --> 00:16:07,550
MAKOTO

186
00:16:15,099 --> 00:16:17,977
[birds chirping]

187
00:16:42,960 --> 00:16:45,046
We'll avenge Aijiro.

188
00:16:49,133 --> 00:16:51,302
You're probably wondering
what I mean.

189
00:16:54,222 --> 00:16:57,475
This whole mess started
because you killed Saeki.

190
00:17:01,312 --> 00:17:04,315
Someone was pulling Saeki's
strings from the shadows.

191
00:17:11,030 --> 00:17:13,824
And that same person
took Eisaburo's life.

192
00:17:16,953 --> 00:17:18,329
What do you mean?

193
00:17:20,998 --> 00:17:22,250
So...

194
00:17:23,417 --> 00:17:25,503
what's with the formal assembly?

195
00:17:27,255 --> 00:17:29,298
Yes, what gives? This is creepy.

196
00:17:38,683 --> 00:17:40,059
I'm sorry for the wait.

197
00:17:42,228 --> 00:17:44,480
Nagakura!

198
00:17:52,947 --> 00:17:54,240
Sorry.

199
00:18:07,044 --> 00:18:08,713
Everyone's here now.

200
00:18:17,972 --> 00:18:19,765
We're going to discipline

201
00:18:21,767 --> 00:18:24,312
the Shinsengumi vice-commander,
Niimi Nishiki.

202
00:18:25,938 --> 00:18:27,231
Huh?

203
00:18:29,609 --> 00:18:31,193
Tell us why.

204
00:18:32,236 --> 00:18:33,654
Niimi Nishiki...

205
00:18:35,323 --> 00:18:38,242
is a traitor who was colluding
with the Choshu.

206
00:18:42,163 --> 00:18:44,206
And this letter

207
00:18:45,583 --> 00:18:46,792
is the proof.

208
00:18:52,715 --> 00:18:54,342
Niimi enlisted help

209
00:18:55,259 --> 00:18:57,762
from Kusaka Genzui of Choshu

210
00:18:59,472 --> 00:19:02,767
who sent Saeki Matasaburo,
an assassin, from his clan

211
00:19:02,850 --> 00:19:05,936
and plotted to annihilate
our Kondo faction.

212
00:19:11,025 --> 00:19:13,444
He murdered Sasaki Aijiro.

213
00:19:19,825 --> 00:19:21,661
Furthermore,

214
00:19:21,744 --> 00:19:25,456
in order to spy on our movements
and those of the Aizu...

215
00:19:30,795 --> 00:19:32,630
he used Abiru Eisaburo...

216
00:19:36,926 --> 00:19:38,636
and once he was
no longer useful,

217
00:19:41,889 --> 00:19:43,182
he murdered him.

218
00:19:49,689 --> 00:19:51,023
That letter...

219
00:19:51,107 --> 00:19:52,775
How did you get
your hands on it?

220
00:19:54,151 --> 00:19:55,403
Someone as cautious as Niimi

221
00:19:55,486 --> 00:19:57,405
wouldn't let it be taken
so easily.

222
00:19:59,323 --> 00:20:00,783
[Hijikata]
It was Serizawa.

223
00:20:02,201 --> 00:20:03,452
[gasps]

224
00:20:05,037 --> 00:20:07,331
Serizawa told us
everything.

225
00:20:09,291 --> 00:20:13,295
So, Serizawa sold out Niimi?

226
00:20:13,838 --> 00:20:15,005
What for?

227
00:20:16,924 --> 00:20:18,592
He's probably just enjoying it.

228
00:20:20,136 --> 00:20:24,724
He wants to see what happens
if he pits us against Niimi.

229
00:20:24,807 --> 00:20:26,475
He doesn't even care

230
00:20:26,559 --> 00:20:30,396
if it puts his own life
on the line.

231
00:20:32,022 --> 00:20:33,691
That's the impression
he gave me.

232
00:20:37,027 --> 00:20:39,613
What is wrong with that guy?

233
00:20:39,697 --> 00:20:41,824
[Saito]
That doesn't matter right now.

234
00:20:44,660 --> 00:20:47,329
Vengeance for
Eisaburo and Aijiro.

235
00:20:48,998 --> 00:20:50,332
Niimi will be cut.

236
00:20:51,709 --> 00:20:52,793
End of story.

237
00:20:53,836 --> 00:20:55,379
Hajime is right.

238
00:21:00,634 --> 00:21:01,677
However...

239
00:21:02,762 --> 00:21:05,139
To be blunt,
our chances of winning

240
00:21:05,222 --> 00:21:06,640
are practically zero.

241
00:21:08,684 --> 00:21:09,602
How come?

242
00:21:11,061 --> 00:21:13,522
If the Shinsengumi
splits into two

243
00:21:13,564 --> 00:21:15,983
most of the men
will likely side with them.

244
00:21:17,276 --> 00:21:19,236
And I hear Niimi is using money

245
00:21:19,320 --> 00:21:24,742
to hire unemployed
Imperialist ronin and bandits.

246
00:21:26,160 --> 00:21:29,413
Even a conservative estimate
puts them...

247
00:21:32,249 --> 00:21:33,667
at 150.

248
00:21:35,044 --> 00:21:36,754
In contrast...

249
00:21:39,173 --> 00:21:41,509
there are only ten of us here.

250
00:21:46,889 --> 00:21:48,390
[chuckles]

251
00:21:52,520 --> 00:21:54,605
One hundred and fifty
against ten, huh?

252
00:21:59,068 --> 00:22:00,236
So that's--

253
00:22:00,319 --> 00:22:01,946
Fifteen men each.

254
00:22:15,751 --> 00:22:16,919
Somehow...

255
00:22:19,630 --> 00:22:22,383
I think I'd almost forgotten.

256
00:22:28,973 --> 00:22:29,974
Back...

257
00:22:31,475 --> 00:22:32,810
at our humble dojo...

258
00:22:36,313 --> 00:22:37,481
when everyone looked down

259
00:22:37,565 --> 00:22:39,692
on our "country-bumpkin"
swordsmanship...

260
00:22:41,110 --> 00:22:43,696
why did we even come to Kyo
in the first place?

261
00:22:48,784 --> 00:22:50,953
Was it for money?
For fame and success?

262
00:22:52,329 --> 00:22:56,667
To play political games
and fight for power?

263
00:23:01,338 --> 00:23:02,798
Of course not.

264
00:23:08,262 --> 00:23:09,722
I came to Kyo
to show all of Japan

265
00:23:09,805 --> 00:23:11,682
that we're the strongest
there is!

266
00:23:13,350 --> 00:23:15,769
That we of the Shieikan

267
00:23:15,853 --> 00:23:20,357
are the strongest and truest
of samurai.

268
00:23:20,441 --> 00:23:23,777
[♪♪♪]

269
00:23:24,695 --> 00:23:27,072
No matter what it takes...

270
00:23:29,366 --> 00:23:30,826
I will avenge Eisaburo

271
00:23:35,331 --> 00:23:37,958
and Aijiro!

272
00:23:48,510 --> 00:23:50,137
I need every one of you...

273
00:23:54,350 --> 00:23:56,018
I want you with me.

274
00:24:08,739 --> 00:24:09,740
Boss.

275
00:24:16,413 --> 00:24:19,583
You don't have to bow for us
anymore.

276
00:24:28,050 --> 00:24:29,051
Hey.

277
00:24:35,432 --> 00:24:37,101
Now that's
what I'm talking about.

278
00:24:44,441 --> 00:24:46,443
Bring on 20 men, or 30.

279
00:24:46,527 --> 00:24:49,363
I'll cut every last one
of them down.

280
00:24:49,446 --> 00:24:52,574
[♪♪♪]

281
00:25:00,457 --> 00:25:04,628
You're as reckless as ever.

282
00:25:07,381 --> 00:25:08,632
But this time,

283
00:25:09,758 --> 00:25:11,802
it's actually quite...

284
00:25:15,055 --> 00:25:16,306
reassuring.

285
00:25:17,725 --> 00:25:18,892
[chuckles softly]

286
00:25:24,106 --> 00:25:25,232
All right.

287
00:25:30,487 --> 00:25:31,655
And...

288
00:25:33,073 --> 00:25:34,783
do we have a plan?

289
00:25:36,493 --> 00:25:38,287
What a stupid question.

290
00:25:38,328 --> 00:25:41,415
Don't you dare lump me in
with you.

291
00:25:41,498 --> 00:25:43,834
Right. That's true.

292
00:25:47,379 --> 00:25:49,548
[soft chatter]

293
00:25:52,718 --> 00:25:54,261
Here's the plan.

294
00:25:55,387 --> 00:25:58,766
Tomorrow, at dusk.

295
00:25:58,849 --> 00:26:02,644
Lord Katamori and Kondo
are set to meet privately

296
00:26:02,728 --> 00:26:04,354
to devise a plan.

297
00:26:05,522 --> 00:26:07,149
The location is Shishigatani.

298
00:26:07,232 --> 00:26:11,820
Katamori will use falconry
as a cover to get himself there.

299
00:26:13,322 --> 00:26:15,783
[mimicking Yamanami]
To avoid being seen,
his guard detail

300
00:26:15,866 --> 00:26:17,659
will be kept to a bare minimum.

301
00:26:21,371 --> 00:26:22,331
[normally]
Money.

302
00:26:23,749 --> 00:26:26,376
I never thought
such a perfect opportunity

303
00:26:26,460 --> 00:26:29,129
would fall right into my lap.

304
00:26:30,547 --> 00:26:32,508
That bastard Serizawa.

305
00:26:32,549 --> 00:26:36,720
Just you watch.
I'm not going down like this!

306
00:26:38,055 --> 00:26:41,725
I'll take Katamori's head
to Choshu as a trophy!

307
00:26:47,689 --> 00:26:49,233
Tomorrow!

308
00:26:49,316 --> 00:26:54,029
We take the head of the Lord
of Aizu, Matsudaira Katamori!

309
00:26:54,113 --> 00:26:56,615
[♪♪♪]

310
00:26:56,698 --> 00:26:59,201
Take as much as you want!

311
00:26:59,284 --> 00:27:01,829
[clamoring]

312
00:27:08,585 --> 00:27:09,837
This energy...

313
00:27:09,920 --> 00:27:13,048
It reminds me of our days
as bandits.

314
00:27:15,425 --> 00:27:17,094
With this crew,

315
00:27:17,177 --> 00:27:22,182
I can take down Kondo
and Serizawa any time I want.

316
00:27:24,601 --> 00:27:27,146
[♪♪♪]

317
00:28:22,910 --> 00:28:25,454
FRONT GATE, BACK GATE

318
00:28:25,495 --> 00:28:28,165
[Niimi]
This is the rendezvous point.

319
00:28:28,248 --> 00:28:32,628
It's surrounded by a deep,
water-filled moat

320
00:28:32,669 --> 00:28:37,841
and has two entrances,
front and back.

321
00:28:42,471 --> 00:28:46,308
Katamori and Kondo both arrived
about 15 minutes ago.

322
00:28:47,142 --> 00:28:48,185
I see.

323
00:28:49,937 --> 00:28:51,146
If we're going to attack,

324
00:28:51,230 --> 00:28:53,065
shouldn't we go in
through the back?

325
00:28:53,148 --> 00:28:56,276
The back entrance is down
a steep path. It's sealed shut.

326
00:28:57,861 --> 00:29:00,280
So, you're saying we have
to bust through the front?

327
00:29:00,322 --> 00:29:02,032
[Yamazaki]
That's correct.

328
00:29:03,158 --> 00:29:04,368
Not a problem.

329
00:29:06,411 --> 00:29:08,497
We'll storm them all at once!

330
00:29:08,580 --> 00:29:11,333
[all shouting]

331
00:29:18,715 --> 00:29:19,883
Listen.

332
00:29:21,426 --> 00:29:23,345
Don't make a sound.

333
00:29:23,428 --> 00:29:25,013
Got it.

334
00:29:25,055 --> 00:29:26,223
Let's go.

335
00:29:45,575 --> 00:29:46,910
[knocks softly]

336
00:30:05,387 --> 00:30:07,472
[shouting, groaning inside]

337
00:30:07,556 --> 00:30:08,849
What's going on?

338
00:30:18,066 --> 00:30:20,527
[scrambling at door]

339
00:30:23,947 --> 00:30:26,491
Boss! It's an ambush!

340
00:30:27,451 --> 00:30:29,870
An ambush? Move!

341
00:30:31,788 --> 00:30:32,956
Move!

342
00:30:36,460 --> 00:30:40,005
[♪♪♪]

343
00:31:01,318 --> 00:31:02,361
Katamori!

344
00:31:03,236 --> 00:31:04,905
What is the meaning of this?

345
00:31:19,878 --> 00:31:22,547
Is this your scheme, Yamanami?

346
00:31:43,026 --> 00:31:47,989
We will now begin
the purge of Niimi Nishiki.

347
00:31:52,661 --> 00:31:55,747
You've got a lot of nerve,
taking on all of us.

348
00:31:55,831 --> 00:31:57,999
You damn runts!

349
00:31:59,334 --> 00:32:02,838
Don't flinch!
Slaughter them all!

350
00:32:02,921 --> 00:32:04,548
[clamoring]

351
00:32:07,426 --> 00:32:10,470
Come at me
with everything you've got!

352
00:32:10,554 --> 00:32:12,222
[all shouting]

353
00:32:26,903 --> 00:32:28,238
Bring it!

354
00:33:53,949 --> 00:33:56,868
Not fired up enough?
You bastard!

355
00:33:56,952 --> 00:33:58,203
Get out of here!

356
00:34:38,034 --> 00:34:41,037
Take that!

357
00:34:41,121 --> 00:34:42,872
Thanks, Toshi.
What about?

358
00:34:51,256 --> 00:34:54,050
I cut them down,
and they just keep coming!

359
00:34:54,134 --> 00:34:56,136
"I don't care
if there's 20 or 30 of them,

360
00:34:56,219 --> 00:34:57,304
I'll cut them all down!"

361
00:34:57,387 --> 00:34:59,472
Who was it that said that again?

362
00:34:59,556 --> 00:35:02,434
That was me!

363
00:35:03,602 --> 00:35:07,105
Move! There's only a handful
of them left.

364
00:35:08,064 --> 00:35:11,192
What a pathetic little ploy.

365
00:35:11,234 --> 00:35:14,696
The passage is too narrow,
so we can't attack all at once.

366
00:35:14,738 --> 00:35:18,783
That's why
they deliberately lured us here.

367
00:35:18,867 --> 00:35:21,578
[laughs]

368
00:35:23,079 --> 00:35:25,206
Fools.

369
00:35:25,248 --> 00:35:27,751
Ultimately, they're still
hopelessly outnumbered.

370
00:35:29,502 --> 00:35:31,546
Mushikui!

371
00:35:31,588 --> 00:35:33,465
Attack from the rear!

372
00:35:33,548 --> 00:35:35,133
But isn't that door
never used?

373
00:35:35,216 --> 00:35:37,385
That's precisely
why you're going!

374
00:35:37,469 --> 00:35:40,805
Hit them from behind.
We'll catch them in a pincer.

375
00:35:43,558 --> 00:35:48,229
All right!
My best fighters, on me!

376
00:35:48,313 --> 00:35:50,732
We're going to end this
right now!

377
00:35:50,774 --> 00:35:52,442
[all shout]

378
00:36:06,915 --> 00:36:09,918
Look, they're on the move.
Are we going to be all right?

379
00:36:12,337 --> 00:36:14,214
Everyone's starting
to get exhausted.

380
00:36:14,297 --> 00:36:15,715
Now's our chance to strike!

381
00:36:19,219 --> 00:36:20,970
Not yet!
We stick to the plan!

382
00:36:21,054 --> 00:36:23,264
Your complacency
will get us all killed!

383
00:36:25,058 --> 00:36:26,601
I'm heading around back.

384
00:36:26,685 --> 00:36:27,727
Hijikata!

385
00:36:28,770 --> 00:36:30,438
Have faith in Yamanami!

386
00:36:30,480 --> 00:36:32,440
The tide of this battle
will turn in our favor.

387
00:36:32,524 --> 00:36:34,275
Isn't that right, Yamanami?

388
00:36:34,359 --> 00:36:37,195
Yes, we have the advantage
of the terrain.

389
00:36:41,282 --> 00:36:43,618
[Saito]
Toshi's getting real antsy.

390
00:36:46,287 --> 00:36:50,083
Are you sure we should
be holding back like this?

391
00:36:50,166 --> 00:36:51,876
Yes.

392
00:36:51,960 --> 00:36:53,920
Remember what Yamanami said?

393
00:36:54,003 --> 00:36:57,674
If we move before the signal,
it'll all be for nothing.

394
00:37:06,683 --> 00:37:09,310
That was a hell of a climb.
Yes.

395
00:37:09,352 --> 00:37:11,980
So this is the
"door that never opens," huh?

396
00:37:12,021 --> 00:37:13,523
Go on, bust it open.

397
00:37:17,318 --> 00:37:19,821
[ronin 1]
Coming in.

398
00:37:23,658 --> 00:37:25,243
[scythe slicing]

399
00:37:26,786 --> 00:37:29,038
It's a demon wind!
[ronin 2] What was that?

400
00:37:36,212 --> 00:37:39,758
No, it's far more vicious
than that.

401
00:37:39,841 --> 00:37:41,760
That's the Grim Reaper.

402
00:37:41,843 --> 00:37:44,220
[♪♪♪]

403
00:37:44,304 --> 00:37:45,889
It's Harada Sanosuke.

404
00:37:48,183 --> 00:37:50,268
You bastard, get down here!

405
00:37:50,351 --> 00:37:51,936
[ronin shouting]

406
00:37:52,020 --> 00:37:54,397
Idiot!
Don't go near him carelessly.

407
00:38:00,570 --> 00:38:01,863
Hey!

408
00:38:20,131 --> 00:38:21,758
Not a single one of you...

409
00:38:24,093 --> 00:38:26,679
is getting past me.

410
00:38:29,140 --> 00:38:31,851
[ronin murmuring fearfully]

411
00:38:31,935 --> 00:38:36,272
Why are you shaking?!
It's just one guy!

412
00:38:36,356 --> 00:38:39,943
Surround him
and cut him to pieces!

413
00:38:40,026 --> 00:38:42,320
[ronin shouting]

414
00:39:01,381 --> 00:39:02,423
[groans]

415
00:39:02,507 --> 00:39:03,925
[blood splatters]

416
00:40:00,356 --> 00:40:01,566
Toshi!

417
00:40:04,527 --> 00:40:06,070
How much longer?

418
00:40:06,154 --> 00:40:07,155
This is endless.

419
00:40:08,990 --> 00:40:11,701
[Mushikui]
No matter how strong you are

420
00:40:11,784 --> 00:40:15,038
when you're seriously fighting
a whole group

421
00:40:15,121 --> 00:40:16,998
your heart gets heavy

422
00:40:17,081 --> 00:40:20,001
and your body stops moving
the way it should.

423
00:40:22,211 --> 00:40:26,174
Because you're skilled,
you won't get an easy death.

424
00:40:27,550 --> 00:40:29,218
You'll fade out
little by little.

425
00:40:31,387 --> 00:40:33,640
This is it, Harada.

426
00:40:35,391 --> 00:40:38,019
Go get him!

427
00:40:38,102 --> 00:40:40,146
[ronin shout]

428
00:40:40,980 --> 00:40:42,398
[shouts]

429
00:40:42,482 --> 00:40:44,901
[blood splattering]

430
00:40:56,412 --> 00:41:00,375
Kill Harada Sanosuke!

431
00:41:00,416 --> 00:41:01,668
[gasping]

432
00:41:10,802 --> 00:41:13,262
[Yamanami] Are you sure
about this, Harada?

433
00:41:15,890 --> 00:41:17,266
They've got about

434
00:41:18,393 --> 00:41:20,478
about 20, maybe 30 men.

435
00:41:21,646 --> 00:41:24,607
We need to hold the line
at the back gate.

436
00:41:24,691 --> 00:41:26,234
No one gets through.

437
00:41:27,777 --> 00:41:29,570
We should send someone else
with you.

438
00:41:29,612 --> 00:41:31,531
No need.
They'd just be in the way.

439
00:41:32,615 --> 00:41:34,909
I'm more than enough on my own.

440
00:41:34,993 --> 00:41:35,952
Sanosuke.

441
00:41:37,328 --> 00:41:40,540
You're not planning on
sacrificing yourself, are you?

442
00:41:42,625 --> 00:41:45,753
I'm going to avenge
Eisaburo and Aijiro.

443
00:41:47,296 --> 00:41:48,840
That's all this is.

444
00:41:52,427 --> 00:41:53,594
Sanosuke.

445
00:41:56,389 --> 00:42:00,309
I put up another batch of
pickled radishes this morning.

446
00:42:01,894 --> 00:42:03,938
What are you talking about
at a time like this?

447
00:42:04,022 --> 00:42:05,565
Will you tell me

448
00:42:06,816 --> 00:42:08,818
when they're ready to eat again?

449
00:42:12,155 --> 00:42:14,157
If you can't promise me that,

450
00:42:15,491 --> 00:42:17,660
I can't let you guard
the back gate.

451
00:42:24,083 --> 00:42:25,960
The most important thing

452
00:42:26,044 --> 00:42:28,921
is for all of us
to eat together again.

453
00:42:29,005 --> 00:42:31,007
It's not about
being ready to die.

454
00:42:31,090 --> 00:42:34,552
[♪♪♪]

455
00:42:43,394 --> 00:42:45,063
You can promise me that, right?

456
00:42:55,948 --> 00:42:57,200
I know.

457
00:43:04,707 --> 00:43:07,126
A promise to the boss...

458
00:43:07,210 --> 00:43:09,003
[inhales shakily]

459
00:43:09,045 --> 00:43:12,215
And I'm damn well
going to keep it!

460
00:43:18,721 --> 00:43:20,515
[blood splattering]

461
00:43:20,598 --> 00:43:22,683
[wheezing]

462
00:43:22,767 --> 00:43:25,019
What the hell is that?

463
00:43:25,103 --> 00:43:26,938
It's not a sickle?

464
00:43:27,814 --> 00:43:29,774
That's a cheap shot.

465
00:43:31,526 --> 00:43:33,820
There's nothing cheap
about it.

466
00:43:35,363 --> 00:43:40,618
I've always been a spear guy.

467
00:43:42,954 --> 00:43:45,206
[ronin whimpering]
A monster!

468
00:43:45,248 --> 00:43:47,250
Let's get out of here!

469
00:43:48,709 --> 00:43:50,670
I got it.

470
00:43:58,469 --> 00:44:00,972
[ronin]
Mushikui is down!

471
00:44:05,893 --> 00:44:06,894
Go!

472
00:44:08,020 --> 00:44:09,105
Go!

473
00:44:09,188 --> 00:44:13,276
What are you dawdling for?!
Get a move on!

474
00:44:13,359 --> 00:44:14,694
But...

475
00:44:15,653 --> 00:44:18,447
we can't get through that.
Huh?!

476
00:44:18,531 --> 00:44:21,784
What can they possibly do
at this point?

477
00:44:27,540 --> 00:44:31,127
They... made a fortress
out of corpses?

478
00:44:39,135 --> 00:44:46,100
Everything's playing out
your way, Yamanami!

479
00:44:46,309 --> 00:44:49,770
[♪♪♪]

480
00:44:52,231 --> 00:44:55,359
[panting]

481
00:44:55,443 --> 00:44:57,403
Go!

482
00:44:57,486 --> 00:45:00,489
MAKOTO

483
00:45:00,573 --> 00:45:02,158
[Kondo shouting]

484
00:45:04,619 --> 00:45:05,828
Shall we?
Yes.

485
00:45:10,082 --> 00:45:14,170
Don't you dare think you won!

486
00:45:22,178 --> 00:45:24,889
[ronin]
Enemy! We've got company!

487
00:45:26,224 --> 00:45:27,391
An enemy attack?

488
00:45:34,649 --> 00:45:37,068
Niimi!

489
00:45:38,194 --> 00:45:39,278
[shouts]

490
00:45:47,536 --> 00:45:53,042
Hold it! Hey! Go! Hajime!

491
00:45:57,672 --> 00:45:59,882
Drop dead, Niimi!

492
00:45:59,966 --> 00:46:07,014
Come if you dare,
you dumb runts!

493
00:46:09,058 --> 00:46:13,187
[Yoshiaki Dewa's "Chiruran
Shinsengumi Requiem" playing]
